title: ZTE donates 50,000 masks to Ukraine in April 2020
description: On April 9, 2020, 50,000 three-layer medical masks donated by ZTE to Ukraine were held in a warehouse in Beijing to be loaded onto a plane to Ukraine. The masks were eventually delivered to Ukraine. The monetary value of the donation is unknown.
staff_comments: AidData has estimated the transaction amount for this donation based on price catalogues from the World Health Organization (WHO). Please see the TUFF Methodology for additional details.

title: AVIC loans warehouse worth USD 1 million to Government of Ukraine
description: In March and April 2020, the Government of Ukraine received several donations of Covid-19 supplies from Chinese companies. The goods were stored in a warehouse in Beijing prior to being shipped to Ukraine. AVIC loaned Ukraine the warehouse as a form of humanitarian aid. The value of this donation was valued at USD 1 million.

title: Shanxi Province provided a donation of 20,000 and 10,000 surgical masks to Canelones and Paysandú in May 2020
description: On May 27, 2020, the Chinese province of Shanxi gave a donation of 20,000 surgical masks to the department of Canelones and 10,000 surgical masks to the department of Paysandú to assist Uruguay's dealing with COVID-19.   Harvard's Mask Diplomacy Dataset estimated the donation to Canelones to be worth USD 8,000 and the donation to Paysandú to be worth USD 4,000, for a total estimated value of USD 12,000.
staff_comments: 1. The Chinese Embassy article that describes this donation includes a photo with several boxes that have Brazilian flags on their labels, in addition to boxes with Uruguayan flags. This issue warrants further investigation.
combined_text:
# Sector
HEALTH

# Title
Shanxi Province provided a donation of 20,000 and 10,000 surgical masks to Canelones and Paysandú in May 2020

# Description
On May 27, 2020, the Chinese province of Shanxi gave a donation of 20,000 surgical masks to the department of Canelones and 10,000 surgical masks to the department of Paysandú to assist Uruguay's dealing with COVID-19.   Harvard's Mask Diplomacy Dataset estimated the donation to Canelones to be worth USD 8,000 and the donation to Paysandú to be worth USD 4,000, for a total estimated value of USD 12,000.
justification: Project is a healthcare-related donation with no direct environmental or energy transition impact
evidence: Donation of surgical masks for COVID-19 response, healthcare sector focus
